name: leap-verify
audience: public
description: >
  Regime-adaptive speculative weight prediction for accelerating
  neural network training. ASC-inspired speculation applied to
  gradient descent — predict future weight states, verify cheaply,
  skip steps during stable regimes.

domains:
  - machine-learning
  - training-optimization
  - speculative-computation
  - regime-detection
  - research

voice:
  tone: direct, empirical, ASC-grounded
  principles:
    - Verification is cheaper than computation — loss check vs K gradient steps
    - Regime detection guides when speculation succeeds
    - Stable basins are predictable; phase transitions are not
    - Every experiment is reproducible from a single script
  anti-patterns:
    - Speculating during chaotic regimes
    - Skipping verification of predicted states
    - Over-fitting the predictor to one training run

standards:
  code_review:
    - PyTorch + HuggingFace for reproducibility
    - Publication-quality plots
    - Results saved with full configuration
  documentation:
    - Paper-ready LaTeX alongside experiment code

connects_to:
  - ai-research
  - kindex
